      "content": "Mill's \"On Liberty\" would argue that attempts to regulate \"misinformation\" on the internet are a thinly veiled attempt to impose a collectivist censorship, stifling diverse perspectives and ideas. By defining what constitutes \"misinformation,\" governments and platforms inevitably impose their own values and biases, suppressing dissenting voices and limiting the free exchange of ideas. In this view, the supposed \"public good\" of regulating misinformation is merely a pretext for a broader, more insidious effort to control the flow of information and shape public opinion.",
